news.title: Mumbai police seek details of properties rented out by people
news.para: The order came into effect for 60 days from Wednesday and its violators will be booked under relevant section of the Indian Penal Code (IPC), he added.

news.title: Meeting to be held next week about tax discount for self-occupied properties in Pune
news.para: A delegation of BJP leaders, including Pune's guardian minister Chandrakant Patil, former mayor Muralidhar Mohol and MLA Madhuri Misal on Wednesday met Shinde and Fadnavis to discuss the issue raised by various citizens groups recently.

news.title: Housing sales in volume terms grew 11% across seven cities in Q3 FY23: ICRA
news.para: Residential real estate sector saw strong demand in Q3 of FY2023 with 11 per cent year-on-year (YoY) growth in area sold, it added.

news.title: Only 20% housing societies own plots in Maharashtra, rest still with builders
news.para: Majority of these housing societies, around 70,000, are in the Mumbai Metropolitan Region. Societies having conveynance deed or deemed conveyance means they have taken collective ownership of the land from the builder.

news.title: GVK group founder sells two residential properties in Hyderabad for Rs 73.81 crore
news.para: The properties - of 1,386 square yards and 1,426 square yards - in the posh Jubilee Hills were sold to Potukuchi Naga Nandini, the wife of Potukuchi Murali Mohana Rao who has business interests in infrastructure, real estate and agriculture.

news.title: Labdhi Lifestyle to take over Rajesh LifeSpaces' project in Mumbai
news.para: With this acquisition, Labdhi will be the lead developer of the project to be now known as Labdhi Searene, while Rajesh LifeSpaces makes a complete exit. Of the financial partners, JM Financial has already been provided an exit, while Mirae Asset will be repaid in the next few days.

news.title: Bring tax sops back for self-occupied homes: Pune citizens
news.para: A special discount was started in 1970 for self-occupied properties. But it was not notified as an act by any state government. So, the discount was declared illegal by auditors of the Union government and scrapped in 2019.

news.title: Delhi mayor holds meets A&C department officials, reviews schemes related to property tax
news.para: During the meeting, senior officials apprised her about the status of revenue collection, tax policies and challenges faced by the department over the years, they said.

news.title: Mohali development body fetches Rs 1,935 crore from e-auction of properties
news.para: Properties auctioned include group housing, commercial spaces, nursing home, IT industrial plots, Shop Cum Offices and booths situated in different projects of GMADA, such as IT City, Aerocity and other sectors of Mohali.

news.title: In Chandigarh, 30 of 340 houses to be up for bidding, allotment assured
news.para: Of the total 340 flats on offer, 30 apartments will be reserved under the scheme, for which allotment will be done through a bidding process.

news.title: About 750 houses, shops face eviction in Velachery lake in Chennai
news.para: All encroachers have been given time to respond and if the government finds their replies unsatisfactory, they will be evicted, the state water resources department told the National Green Tribunal Southern Zone (NGT SZ).

news.title: CBI arrests Pearls Group's director after his deportation from Fiji
news.para: ​A team of CBI officials had gone to Suva in Fiji to bring Gill after being deported from the archipelago under 'Operation Trishul' and was placed under arrest after landing here, they said.

news.title: Two-year timeline for 50% pending Jaypee projects
news.para: The timeline submitted by the Mumbai-based group proposes to hand over all 24 projects -- 15 are in Noida, eight are near Yamuna Expressway and one is in Agra -- in the next six to 42 months of the plan being approved by NCLT.

news.title: Chandigarh housing board sells 2 BHK for Rs 1 crore in sector 51
news.para: Of 92 commercial leasehold properties on offer, only two got bidders. Both are located in Sector 49B. Each having a reserve price of Rs 43.03 lakh fetched Rs 46.51 lakh.

news.title: Pune citizens clamour for speedy disposal of MahaRERA cases
news.para: A representation was made by citizen groups to chief minister Eknath Shinde and deputy chief minister Devendra Fadnavis last week.
